The difference in the number of words Cam could type in 5 minutes before and after breaking his right arm is 30 words. 


Before breaking his right arm, Cam was able to type at a rate of 9 words per minute.

After breaking his right arm, he used his left hand to type which slowed him down to a rate of 6 words per minute.


To find the difference between these two rates, we can multiply the number of minutes (5) by the difference in speed: 
9 words per minute - 6 words per minute = 30 words/minute. 


Therefore, Cam could type 30 more words after breaking his right arm than before he broke it.
